The struggle stalwart&#8217;s family says she went to the Milpark Hospital for a routine medical check-up on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG African National Congress struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela has been admitted to the Milpark Hospital for observation.Her family says she went to hospital for a routine medical check-up on Wednesday.In December, Madikizela-Mandela was discharged from the same facility, but the nature of her ailment then was unconfirmed.Her spokesperson Victor Dlamini says: The doctors have decided to admit her for further observation. We are pleased to announce a clean bill of health. She is undergoing quite a number of tests, given her own medical history, but there s nothing to worry about. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)